result.adr_address: 18 Harcourt Rd, Admiralty, Hong Kong
result.name: mixian sense

reviews.text: Nice noodles here. Soup is very rich in tomato and flavour is good. Pig intestine is very tender and nice, pork balls are good too.

Wow one word. It was so delicious and good amazing food. We had 3 dishes.  Veggie soup with noodles, and 2 dishes of pork meat soup with noodles and pork chops in another bowl.  We ordered also 3 fabulous drinks of tea. 190 HKD. AMAZING PLACE.  Highly Recommended. This restuarant is inside a shopping mall so they have outside the restaurant the WC of the mall. Accessible for wheelchair. Very good food . Go and eat in this place.
Try the tomato soup. That’s the best
Price of afternoon tea is reasonable
Love the variety of noodle to choose , different type of soup base and ingredients to go along! Cosy and valuable place in Admiralty.

result.adr_address: Infinitus Plaza, Des Voeux Rd Central, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: Infinitus Plaza, Des Voeux Rd Central, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Infinitus Plaza Shopping Arcade

reviews.text: Pretty much just a place for a coffee or yum cha, and maybe buy a few stuff after work too
A very small mall connected to Sheung Wan mtr station. Good and convenient location. Bus stops for buses going to different places are just in front of the mall.
The mall is nothing special but very useful to access bridge to IFC and Macau Ferry.
Useful shops.. love MiniSo & Pret. Very friendly staff. We had a baby stroller so 1 staff member assisted me to service lift and was very helpful.

Personally I like this small shopping plaza, but it's not really a place to go shopping. There's a coffee shop, 7eleven and some small gift shops, besides a couple of restaurants. That is the extent of it. Facilities are clean and it connects directly into Sheung Wan MTR station and the walking bridge to IFC Mall as well as the Rumsey Street Parking Garage, so that's a plus. Staff are friendly but there is no real info desk.
